Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Combine vegetables, dressing and rosemary; spread onto baking sheet. Bake 40 min. or until vegetables are tender and golden brown, stirring occasionally. Place water, broth and 3/4 cup cream cheese cubes in large saucepan; cook on medium heat 3 min., stirring frequently with whisk until mixture is well blended. Stir in vegetables. Blend soup, in batches, in blender until smooth. Return to saucepan; bring to boil. Thin soup with additional water, if desired. Serve topped with remaining cream cheese cubes.